==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turgent
<hw>Tur"gent</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r"j⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>turgens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>turgere</ets> to
swell.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rising into a tumor, or a puffy state;
swelling; tumid; <as>as, <ex>turgent</ex> humors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inflated; bombastic; turgid; pompous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Recompensed with <qex>turgent</qex> titles.</q>
<rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turgesce</ent>⟦br⟧
